other_tests.findings: The appendix is dilated up to 12 mm and fluid filled with several appendicoliths including a 6-mm appendicolith at the base, a 4-mm appendicolith in the mid portion and a 6-mm appendicolith near the tip. There is adjacent stranding. No free intraperitoneal air or ascites. The liver, spleen, pancreas, adrenal glands, kidneys, and visualized portions of the ureters are unremarkable.
